USDA Organic

USDA Organic

USDA Organic is protected by law, inspected by experts, traced from farm to store, and shaped by public input. USDA develops and enforces the organic standards, which require products to be produced using farming practices that maintain and improve soil and water quality, minimize the use of synthetic materials, conserve biodiversity, and avoid genetic engineering, among other factors. Crops can be certified organic if theyre grown without prohibited substances such as most synthetic fertilizers and pesticides for three years prior to harvest. Livestock are raised on pasture and treated humanely without growth hormones or antibiotics. Organic products do not contain GMOs or artificial colors, flavors, or preservatives. Products that contain a minimum of 95 percent organic ingredients and use the USDA Organic seal are part of Climate Pledge Friendly.

Learn more about this certification

From the manufacturer


About GREEN & BLACK'S

GREEN & BLACKS is a chocolate brand founded on sustainable and ethical cocoa sourcing principles, based on our conviction that great taste comes from the finest ingredients. Green symbolizes our commitment to always sourcing ethical cocoa. Black stands for our high quality and the delicious intensity of our chocolate.

GREEN & BLACKS Chocolate

Expertly crafted using the finest ingredients.

GREEN & BLACK'S Organic is USDA Organic, Fair Trade, and UN Certified Ethically Sourced chocolate*. The rich taste comes from the full, dynamic flavor characteristics of Trinitariococoa beans. We take great pride in creating distinctively smooth and rich chocolate experiences.

  • Learn more about GREEN & BLACKS ethically sourced cocoa at the official website
  • *Client Code: pr276100 Date Issued: 02/08/2018 CCOF Certified Since: 06/01/2002

Product Description

A unique combination of cocoa, sugar and cocoa butter, Green & Blacks 70% cocoa bittersweet dark chocolate strikes a delicious balance between the intensity of our darkest blends and the creaminess of milk chocolates. We use only the finest organic ingredients and take extra time and care to bring out the delicious flavor that has become our trademark. Grab a 10-pack to so you always have this delectable taste treat on hand.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    5.0 out of 5 stars Great Dark chocolate, product arrived in tact.
    Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2016
    Size: 3.5 Ounce (Pack of 10)Verified Purchase
    I was looking for a new dark chocolate after the report came out about levels of Cadmium and Lead in some of the other popular brands of Dark chocolate. I decided to try this one out and am incredibly happy with my purchase. It tastes just like a dark chocolate should and is organic and fair trade. I also loved that it was shipped with a cold pack and wrapped in a material to keep the product cold in transfer. Considering the weather has been in the 90's the past week, I was alittle concerned about this, but because of their packing, it arrived in great condition. Would definitely recommend.

    EDIT: After this initial order I ordered this again and unfortunately that batch we old and not edible. I tried several of the bars out of the box and they were all the same. I contacted the company and within a few minutes they apologized and refunded the money. I decided to give them another shot and re-ordered them and this new batch is just as delicious as the first batch, so I am keeping my 5 star review because the company had great service and the bars are great.

  • W.Ryan
    5.0 out of 5 stars Incomparable Dark Chocolate
    Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2015
    Size: 3.5 Ounce (Pack of 10)Verified Purchase
    I am a lover of dark chocolate and have searched for and tried every brand I could find. In general, I find 85% dark chocolates too bitter for my taste. I prefer dark chocolate that is intensely chocolate with a bit of sweetness, which I have found in chocolates in the 65% to 75% range. Of these the G&B 70% stands apart from all of the others I have tried for the complexity of its chocolate flavors, which I am no more able to label as I am the flavors found in fine wine.
    As one would expect in a 70% dark chocolate, the flavor is intensely chocolate, as is typical of bars in this class. What separates and elevates G&B above all others is the unfolding of flavors as it melts in your mouth, a trait I have only found elsewhere in the very best gourmet chocolate truffles, such as Christopher Elbow's and Andre's Grand Cru, both of which are very expensive. This is not to say G&B is in the same class as gourmet dark chocolate truffles, obviously it is not. It does however, share a complexity of flavor not found in other chocolate bars, which is why it is by far my favorite chocolate bar.
    I might add, I too have bought G&B chocolate bars that were inedible due to improper storage. In my case, they came from a local store of a very well known large organic grocery store chain.
